# Notebook Rules

## Structure
- Notebooks are for exploration and parameter tuning only.
- All logic lives in src/. Notebooks call src/ functions, never reimplement them.
- If a notebook cell has more than 5 lines of non-trivial logic, move it to src/.

## Cell Design
- Each cell must be independently re-runnable after the setup cells at the top.
- Store intermediates in clearly named variables.
- Do NOT use !shell commands.
- Do NOT call plt.show() — return Figure objects.

## Allowed Hardcoded Values (notebooks only)
- K = 10  # TUNE THIS  — top-k muscles to plot
- SAMPLE_IDX = 0  # TUNE THIS  — sequence to inspect
- DRY_RUN = False  # TUNE THIS  — skip OpenSim when True
